    "shortDescription": "<p>You place a willing subject into a cataleptic state. It remains aware of its surroundings but is paralyzed, appearing dead unless observers make a DC 20 Heal check. <i>Hibernate</i> delays the effects of poison, disease, and bleed effects for the spell's duration, and half of any hit point damage suffered by the subject is converted to nonlethal damage.</p><p>This spell originated with the Green Faith, but has spread to all other druidic religions.</p>"
